In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1⁄4 cups water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim and peel @Carrots{6%ounce}. Using a #peeler{}, shave carrots lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the core; discard core. Trim and halve @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Peel and mince @Ginger{1%thumb} and @Garlic{1%clove}.

== Pickled Scallions ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @White Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Sesame Oil{1%tablespoon}, @Gochujang Sauce{1/2%ounce}, half the @Soy Sauce{2%tablespoon}, and @Sugar{1%tablespoon}. Stir until sugar has dissolved.

== Vegetables ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add carrots; season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Add another drizzle of oil to pan. Add zucchini; season with salt and pepper. Cook until browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside with carrots.

== Beef ==

> Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Cook through this step as instructed, swapping in chicken (no need to break up chicken into pieces!) or beef for pork.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, ginger, and garlic. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until pork is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add remaining soy sauce and cook, stirring, until liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper; divide between bowls. Arrange pork and veggies over rice. Top with pickled scallion whites (and pickling liquid). Drizzle with sauce. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.